<main class="container">
  <div class="jumbotron">
    <center><h1 style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 20px;">Here you will find my latest Projects!</h1></center>
  </div>
</main>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>My Projects</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 20px;
      background-color: lightcyan;
    }
    
    h1 {
      color: #333;
      font-size: 28px;
      margin: 20px 0;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 24px;
      color: #333;
      margin: 20px 0 10px;
    }
    
    .project {
      margin-bottom: 40px;
      text-align: center;
      display: none;
    }
    
    .project.active {
      display: block;
    }

    .project img {
      max-width: 100%;
      height: auto;
      border: 1px solid #ddd;
      border-radius: 8px;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
      transition: transform 0.2s;
      cursor: pointer;
    }

    .project img:hover {
      transform: scale(1.05);
    }

    .project h2 {
      font-size: 24px;
      margin: 20px 0 10px;
      color: #333;
    }

    .project p {
      color: #333;
      font-size: 16px;
      line-height: 1.5;
      margin-top: 10px;
      margin-left: 20px;
      margin-right: 20px;
      text-align: center; /* Centering the paragraph text */
    }

    .project-divider {
      border-top: 2px solid #ddd;
      margin: 20px 0;
    }

    .project-navigation {
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }

    .project-navigation button {
      background-color: #333;
      color: white;
      border: none;
      padding: 10px 20px;
      margin: 0 10px;
      cursor: pointer;
      border-radius: 5px;
      font-size: 16px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="project active">
    <h2>Personalized Portfolio for My Girlfriend</h2>
    <img src="img/portfolio.png" alt="Personalized Portfolio for My Girlfriend" width="300">
    <p>I crafted a visually captivating personalized digital portfolio, seamlessly blending web design and development.
      Leveraging HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript, I created a dynamic platform that elegantly showcases her artwork, photography, and detailed
      biographical information. The portfolio boasts a responsive design, ensuring a flawless user experience across devices, and integrates
      a content management system for effortless updates, spotlighting my technical expertise in front-end and back-end web technologies.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="project">
    <h2>Office Room Reservation System</h2> 
    <img src="img/booking.png" alt="Office Room Reservation System image" width="300">
    <p>In 2022, I undertook the development of a comprehensive room reservation system for a co-working office in Brazil. 
      Leveraging my expertise in PHP and Laravel, I created a robust solution that streamlines the booking of meeting rooms,
      private offices, and shared spaces within the co-working environment. This project was entirely self-driven,
     from conceptualization to implementation, and it is now an integral part of the office's daily operations. 
     The system has significantly improved efficiency and resource management, allowing employees and clients to reserve office
     spaces effortlessly, ultimately enhancing the co-working experience.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="project">
    <h2>Family-Friendly Alexa Clone with Location Sharing</h2>
    <img src="img/cloneapp.jpeg" alt="Project 3" width="300">
    <p>I engineered a family-oriented Alexa-like voice assistant that goes beyond typical smart speakers. Developed using
      natural language processing (NLP) and cloud-based technologies, this innovative assistant facilitates seamless voice
      interactions for users. What sets it apart is its location-sharing feature, driven by geolocation services and authentication
      protocols, enabling real-time updates on family members' whereabouts and availability. This project underscores my ability to
      harness emerging technologies to create solutions that enrich family connectivity and simplify daily life.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="project-divider"></div>

  <div class="project-navigation">
    <button onclick="prevProject()">Previous</button>
    <button onclick="nextProject()">Next</button>
  </div>
</body>
<script>
  let currentProject = 0;
  const projects = document.querySelectorAll('.project');

  function showProject(index) {
    projects.forEach((project, i) => {
      if (i === index) {
        project.classList.add('active');
      } else {
        project.classList.remove('active');
      }
    });
  }

  function nextProject() {
    currentProject++;
    if (currentProject >= projects.length) {
      currentProject = 0;
    }
    showProject(currentProject);
  }

  function prevProject() {
    currentProject--;
    if (currentProject < 0) {
      currentProject = projects.length - 1;
    }
    showProject(currentProject);
  }
</script>
</html>

